<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of the many things that people blamed for =
the 2008 financial crisis was bank bonuses. The idea was that a lot of bank=
ers and traders at investment banks got most of their pay in the form of va=
riable year-end bonuses, so they would take a lot of risk in order to get a=
 big bonus: If their risky bets worked out, they=E2=80=99d share in the gai=
