<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The normal way for a venture capital firm to i=
nvest in a startup company is something like this. The startup is a=C2=A0<e=
m>corporation</em>, and it issues=C2=A0<em>stock</em>, and the VC firm (thr=
ough one of its funds) buys the stock. The VC firm might get a seat on the =
startup=E2=80=99s board of directors, and might have some say in running th=
e startup. But the startup is a separate company. If it is doing bad stuff,=
 the VC firm could lose the money it invested in the startup, but it will n=
ot ordinarily get in trouble for the startup=E2=80=99s actions. When startu=
ps like Theranos and FTX collapsed in scandal, the VC firms that bought the=
ir stock were treated as=C2=A0<em>victims=C2=A0</em>of the scandals, not=C2=
=A0<em>co-conspirators</em>.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then the way the VC firm makes money is by=
 eventually selling their stock, when the startup goes public or is bought =
by a bigger company.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the crypto boom, VC firms discovered a diff=
erent way to invest in startups. The startup would be a=C2=A0<em>crypto pro=
ject</em>, and it would issue=C2=A0<em>tokens</em>, and the VC firm would b=
uy the tokens. The tokens might have some governance rights: The crypto pro=
ject might be a DAO, a decentralized autonomous organization, whose token h=
olders get to vote on what it should do.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The advantages of this structure, for VCs, wer=
e:=C2=A0</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Crypto tokens, DAOs, web3, etc.=C2=A0=
got a lot of hype, so in 2021 you could buy these tokens and resell them fo=
r more of a profit than you might get by investing in normal stock in norma=
l startups.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You could sell=C2=A0<e=
m>faster:=C2=A0</em>Crypto tokens lived, or seemed to live, in a weird regu=
latory gray area, so you could buy the crypto project=E2=80=99s tokens, say=
 to yourself =E2=80=9Cahhh these tokens are not=C2=A0<em>securities</em>, <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33130424.259419/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMTcvYnJhbm=
NoZXMtbWFrZS1iYW5rLXJ1bnMtaGFyZGVyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTAyNCZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb1b637a7" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=09=
=09they are</a> =E2=80=98little more than alphanumeric cryptographic sequen=
ces,=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D and=C2=A0sell them to retail investors on some crypt=
o exchange.=C2=A0Instead of buying stock and waiting for years for a startu=
